<subSubSection pageNumber="324" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="324">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="324">Note:</emphasis>
Dahlgren (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="324">Opera Bot.</emphasis>
21: 213. 1968; in Leistner, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="324">Fl. Southern Africa</emphasis>
16(3:6): 316. 1988) stated that the name was based on 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="324">Tulbagh 29</emphasis>
, which he could not locate. He therefore designated 893.30 (LINN) as a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
. He was evidently unaware of the existence of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tulbagh’s">Tulbagh's</normalizedToken>
specimen (which supports current usage) among the small number of Linnaean sheets at BM and, moreover, appeared to overlook 893.31 (LINN), annotated with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“genistoides”">&quot;genistoides&quot;</normalizedToken>
by Linnaeus which, although it does not support current usage, cannot be dismissed as not being original material.
</paragraph>
